name: Raymond El Khoury
snippet: I don’t know where to begin. The staff is extremely friendly and professional. Very knowledgeable and helpful. We are not very accustomed to this kind of restaurant, and they helped us pick items and the right wine. Steaks were perfectly cooked. Sides were phenomenal. The cheesecake is to die for. Highly recommend for a special night out.

name: Sunil Kadikar
snippet: Trendy and chic, incredibly decadent and lavish. Great place to celebrate a special occasion. Of course amazing steaks as you’d expect. The ceviche was amazing, and the cheesecake dessert was a work of art! Amazing cocktail options and incredible variety of bourbon. Lots of rare options that you can’t find elsewhere.

name: Susie S
snippet: Fantastic Steak and Seafood Restaurant. Service was impeccable, food was outstanding. Drinks and wine were top notch. One of the best restaurants in Toronto. It's a hidden gem in the city. Minutes away from Scotiabank Arena at Bay and Harbour Streets. Great for business meetings, date nights or out with friends. They have an outdoor patio too and a private diningroom. Make reservations ahead of time.

name: Lyndsay Hone
snippet: The best steakhouse in the city. The location of this restaurant is misleading ... we had passed over it in the past simply bc of where it is in the bottom of an apartment building 'away' from the heart of things, but thankful we finally made a point of going! The wine list is extensive and has some excellent options, whatever your pallette. Steaks were perfectly cooked (of course) and again had lots of choice. Sides perfectly balanced - highly recommend the brussel sprouts. Tableside banana foster and a delightful cheesecake was the perfect way to end the meal. Service was impeccable, exactly what one would expect of a 5-star restaurant. Atmosphere is high end and private. Lovely decor, beautiful blues and golds, makes for an overall perfect experience.

name: Cici li
snippet: I have been wanting to try this steakhouse since they opened a couple years ago and must say what an experience! This venue spared no expense, my pallette loved every dish that was served especially the chefs specialty dishes. We got 3 additional samplers that the chef sent out which were perfectly executed! The steaks were recommended by our waiter and may i say excellent choice! They were cooked to perfection, each dish was perfectly executed from taste to presentation, will definitely recommend!

name: W
snippet: Excellent Experience! Will absolutely visit again. The service was A++ server was attentive and very thoughtful. The Butcher Chef offers the best selection of steak in my opinion. We started with the Seafood Platter. The quality of seafood on this platter was extremely fresh, the oysters still have me thinking about it today! Then we went with a 16oz Striploin AA&CO Queensland with 4oz of Wagyu from Miyazaki, Japan as well as 4oz of Kobe with everything being cooked to med-rare perfection. They offer the 4oz option for those wanting to experience a bit of everything, which is a fantastic idea. The sides offered were amazing as well. Definitely worth visiting. I love everything about this restaurant.

name: Ceyla E
snippet: Me and my partner came here for our 1 year and had an amazing experience, all the staff was lovely and the food was mind blowing. The pasta was the best I ever had. Me and my S.O. will return for another anniversary

name: Ray Tran
snippet: Let me start with the amazing service from a great group of staff. Scallop dumpling with Wagyu strip was perfect start to the meal - on the house Tuna and A5 Wagyu tartare was fresh and buttery with the beef Chorizo and clam app had so many depth of flavors and textures - on the house Wagyu ravioli with a super generous of black truffle - melt in your mouth ravioli but the sauce was so rich and flavorful Quebec Duck dry aged for 3 weeks - honestly best duck confit I ever had I will be back again to try everything else

name: Caroline Glavind
snippet: All I can say is this: WOW! I had high expectations for The Butcher Chef after reading reviews and seeing the prices. The food was absolutely outstanding and the venue is intimate. Having experienced some other popular steakhouses of similar caliber in the city (Harbour 60, Blueblood), I can honestly say this was the best steakhouse meal I have ever had in Toronto. For a special occasion, the prices are absolutely worth it. To start, my partner and I ordered the bread, wild shrimp ceviche and caesar salad. The bread was brioche served with some kind of zucchini mixture on top and freshly shaved truffle. I really appreciated that they elevated the experience of having bread with a meal. It was really like it’s own special appetizer. The Caesar salad was very good, although it was the wild shrimp ceviche that really blew me away. The flavour was complex and evolved as it was in your mouth. Hard to explain… but truly outstanding! For our main, we ordered the wild mushrooms, pastrami carrots, 8oz. PEI Tenderloin and Ontario 16 oz. Bone-in Striploin. My partner and I were blown away by the tenderness and flavour of the steaks. My PEI tenderloin had a wonderful salinity and a perfectly executed crust. The dinner for 2 was about $500. Although pricey, it was worth it. Cannot recommend this place enough! So impressed. It is obviously a lot of care has gone into the curation of the experience for the guest. We will definitely be back.

name: Gayan Pathirana
snippet: One fine night, we decided to give this place a try because I basically live above this place. No reservation, just walked in. I got the feeling it was a bit fancy, but when the hostess said “do you want to see a menu first, or are you comfortable”, I was sure it was fancy and a little bit concerned about my wallet. Nonetheless, the t-bone steak was fantastic, and the cheese cake was memorable. The service was really top-notch. The sommelier was on hand to help with the wine selection, and our server knew everything about the beef they were serving. Turns out they have a pretty thick handbook (with pictures) of everything about the beef they serve. They are serious about their meat. The cheesecake was no everyday cheesecake, either. This cheesecake had extra flair. It comes to your table with smoking cold nitrogen. For a walk-in, it was a really amazing experience and totally worth it.

name: Dennis S
snippet: We had a wonderful dinner and our server was extremely pleasant. For appetizers, we had the scallops. This was our favorite dish of the night. For mains, we ordered a Wagyu Steak along with fries. It was delicious and cooked exactly how we like it! For dessert, we had Cheesecake. Have had better cheesecake. Overall, the food by itself would be 3 stars for the price and the additional 1 star is because of how pleasant and friendly our server was.

name: odilliagao
snippet: Celebrated my birthday here and I loved everything about this place. Food was amazing and the staff was even better. Service was excellent. Highly recommend the beef tartare, Miyazaki steak and their Cabernet Sauvignon!

name: Natasha Hüsty
snippet: The food is delicious. The oysters were fresh and meaty. The garnishes for the oysters were also very nice. The steak tartare was delicious too. The espresso martinis are good and not too sweet. A must try.

name: Steven
snippet: The service here is one of the best, if not the best in the city. Very attentive and informative when it comes to all the dishes. Freshly baked brioche is very underrated. I ordered the Quebec Duck for the main dish, definitely a great experience and great staff.

name: A O
snippet: Nice ambience and they have Toto toilets which is great. The cocktails that I tried were really good specially Sea Air on Sunday. Extensive steak menu. I tried the miyazaki striploin medium and l really liked it. I think medium rare would have been good too. I didn't see too many sides/appetizers that I liked and the soup tasted ok but I didn't enjoy it...too runny for me. The dessert (pavlova) was ok a bit stale. I would just order steak and cocktails. They do also have a big wine list. Our server was nice however I did encountered unnecessary drama as soon as I entered. I booked this venue on Sept 14 for Oct 16th on OpenTable for 2 females and provided my credit card info and choose Birthday as the occasion. There were 2 radio buttons: one for indoor dining and another for outdoor which was grayed out (disabled). I obviously chose indoor dining. We arrived on time (6:30) and the hostess informed us that they only have patio seating available. It was a chilly day and raining too. I asked why and she told me because I hadn't booked it in advance and was a last minute booking. I told her I booked it about a month ago. She then said, I had to write my seating preference in the comment box. I felt I was being lied to and disrespected. She talked to her manager and we eventually had our indoor seat but told us we have to leave by 8 which made me feel very uncomfortable since ordering apps/main/dessert can sometimes take longer depending on the kitchen. This was my birthday and I didn't feel welcomed and didn't sense hospitality. When I told my sever he offered a complimentary martini and cheesecake. I appreciate the gesture but felt that the manager was arrogant and that impacts the overall vibe and service. I wish I had a better experience because I do love a good cocktail and steak.

name: Mohamed
snippet: Amazing experience, will definitely go again! From the food to the decor, everything was perfect. The waiters were always thoughtful and ready to help. I rarely review restaurants but this one clearly deserved the 5 stars.

name: Anthony DiCenzo
snippet: Amazing steaks, food and service in a very intimate setting. No expense has been spared in decor and implementation. The new patio is incredible and rain or shine. Definitely a lovely fine dining experience!

name: Richard Tang
snippet: Nothing too outstanding. The dessert lacked layers and depth. The beef and crab appetizer is quite delicious. The rabbit meat was not to my liking. I think for its price, I’m expecting more from the dining experience.

name: Rex Jin
snippet: My wife went in first and I went to park the car. So she was sitting at our table for about 10mins before I came back from parking. I stood at the reception/front desk for about 5 minutes and no one came to greet me. I did not know where my wife was sitting. So I just walked inside myself and saw my wife at the patio. There are servers walking around and just ignored me. After we sit down for 10 minutes, there was no one came to us for water or even a hello. So my wife was sitting there for 25 minutes, without any water or anything. Finally, I did a big wave, and this guy noticed me. The chef was walking around here and there greeting other people like we were transparent. There were also other two gentle men dressing in suite and walked around here and there. I did not know what they were doing. Give me some water at least. My wife said to me, I guess other guests were more important than us. That was not cool.... Finally we decided to try the tasting menu. Without even told us what would be on the menu, he just told me that the tasting menu is expensive, like I could not afford it..... I smiled at him.....really I wanted to slap on his face and show him how much tax I paid last year. Terrible experience for the first half an hour. The food, I have got to be honest, they were amazing. Beautifully presented and prepared. I got the bill and added 15% tips for the food and the girl who actually "served" us. She was the only person nice to us. We left our table walked through the patio to the exit door. No one said thank you/bye/have a good night... Thank you for your "hospitality" and keep treating your customers like this.

name: Cat
snippet: I tried the tasting menu since I did not have that great of an impression for a dish that I had chosen last time. The halibut, duck and Australian striploin dishes were way above my expectation, but the shrimp ceviche appetizer blew my mind. Cocktails and desserts were great and service was up to par. I am glad to have chosen this place to be my first restaurant outing in awhile, I'll be back for more.

name: Mel S
snippet: The wild shrimp ceviche is a great starter! If you’re a fan of ceviche I wouldn’t miss out. You must try it. There is a variety of steak options available. Personally one of the only restaurants I come to for steak because of the consistency. Regularly juicy, flavoursome, and cooked exactly as requested. Management is friendly, servers are timely, and the atmosphere is divine. 0 complaints. Can’t forget the amazing mixology knowledge of the bartenders. Their ability to create new cocktails based on your likings or cravings is impressive.

name: Valeria Mozheyko
snippet: Maybe I had high expectations but this was a little of a disappointment. I love the decor and how the place is small and has only about 10-15 tables, but the food was not impressive. The steak wasn’t worth its money at all, and the sides were very average. The wine was great, the service was meh. I don’t think I would want to come back here or recommend this restaurant.

name: Irene Dimech
snippet: My fav resto to date - should be michelin star rated!! From the staff to the service it's one of a kind restaurant that exceeds perfection!

name: W G
snippet: I’ve been waiting for this place to open, and after an amazing dinner here last night, I’ll say that it was definitely worth the wait! It’s a unique and beautiful boutique steakhouse, hidden away on Harbour St. love that the entire family is involved, from the design and decor to the front of house staff, it speaks to their commitment and passion. The restaurant seats approximately 50, and it’s an intimate experience. They have a unique cocktail menu, and I tried their version of the Sazerac which was accompanied by Absinthe meant to be sipped together. Very unique!! Our amusebouche consisted of a gugère and potato crisp with shellfish - A great way to start off!! Their menu has great options for all, with seafood steak and game meats. Thank you to the staff for asking about and accommodating for food allergies ! Other stellar dishes pictured here are the octopus with chorizo and the succulent Venison - Wow that’s probably the best venison I’ve ever had! You have to try the smoked # carrots and shishito peppers - The smoke and spices definitely take these dishes to the next level! My dinner companions had the heirloom salad and Cornish Hen which were beautifully presented and delicious, as well as the steak which was ‘perfectly done.’ Our portion sizes were quite substantial so although we didn’t stay for dessert, of course I took some to go. The white chocolate cheesecake was beautifully presented, delicious, and a wonderful end to the meal! Overall, an exceptional experience, and one I’ve been waiting to try for years. The wait was worth it! Great job by this team overall and I wish you success on this journey!! I’ll be back!

name: Riana McBride
snippet: One of my new favourite restaurants in Toronto! Their tasting menu was absolutely amazing. The restaurant has such a nice environment, the staff is incredibly friendly and professional, and the food is some of the best I’ve ever had. If you like cocktails, I would highly recommend the Breakfast in Paris!

name: Brandon Varga
snippet: Decided to try this restaurant for a birthday and the experience was really disappointing. We decided to try the tasting menu. For 350 dollars a person, you would expect high quality dishes with lots of taste and flavour. Unfortunately, this did not deliver at all. The lobster and carpaccio dish tasted extremely fishy. The next dish was an asparagus dish. This was under cooked / not seasoned at all. When describing the tasting menu, they told us it would come with two steak dishes. A waygu shortrib and a wagyu steak/ mushroom dish. Come to find out that they did not have the shortrib and instead we would get a veal dish. The veal was so fatty and tough, I could not finish it. The waygu and mushroom dish was room temperature when we received it, not hot at all. For a steak restaurant, I hoped that that would be the star of the tasting menu but both plates were just not done well. To walk out of a restaurant and spend 1,000 dollars to have cold steak is just not acceptable.

name: Farhan Munshi
snippet: As a steak lover I had very high hopes for this place. Comparing it to Jacobs I didn’t find the steak that good, best thing on the menu was the A5 tartar. Service was very average. Sever messed up a lot. Sides were not good, cheesecake was good though, being in the same family as micheals on Simcoe I had a much better experience there. Will not return.

name: Alessandra Palombo
snippet: What a great experience. From the complimentary parking (which was amazing because i went to the game after dinner) to the outstanding meal and service. I cant stop talking about it. The food was just to die for and the Chef came right to our table and served one of our courses!!!

name: Matthew Shortt
snippet: Tried calling, they never picked up. Called another day, they said that wasn't a good day to get a gift card, so come another day. Called the day and time they said was "okay" to confirm someone was available before 5pm to let me in to buy it, they told me not to come (come another day). I guess I'm not going.

name: Andrew Daw
snippet: The epitome of class. I have been beyond impressed from my visits to The Butcher Chef, from the second you walk in, the cheerful greeting at the host stand to being shown your table and every step of service. These people know what they’re doing. My girlfriend and I enjoyed a beautiful dinner the night before the lockdown started and couldn’t have been happier. We enjoyed the beef tartare and were treated to this incredible bread/butter/cheese and bacon dish (so tasty). Their Bar director Ben is beyond talented and we loved all of their cocktails but especially the “5 O’Clock Tea” which was made with a green tea infused Crystal Head Vodka and their “worlds best amaretto sour” with Signal Hill Whisky. I also enjoyed a nice Boulevardier, possibly the best Margarita I’ve had since moving to Toronto and their “Apple of my eye”cocktail. Their tented patio was really well done and was very warm ! Can’t wait to visit them again soon !

name: Charbel Boutros
snippet: From the moment we walked in, the service was impeccable. The wait staff was very knowledgeable on the food and menu. We asked a lot of questions and they were very responsive. The food was out of this world. Presentation was 10/10 and the flavours all blended so well together. I have never been to a place that pays so much attention to detail. And the BATHROOMS… heated toilet seats… enough said. Thank you to the Chefs and amazing staff for making our night a memorable one that we won’t soon forget!

name: Noel Rodrigues
snippet: The staff is well versed and simply go out of their way in making your experience most comfortable and rewarding. Looking forward to another visit.

name: Catherine Lindley
snippet: A wonderful restaurant with impeccable service. Food was amazing! Will definitely return!

name: Carstin Hao
snippet: Had the tasting menu. Food was amazing and everything was really well cooked but if you're going to charge $300 for it I think you should ensure I'm leaving the restaurant with a full stomach. Not enough food!

name: Austinslife
snippet: As I sit here in this restaurant, I am absolutely amazed at how elegant and sophisticated the atmosphere is. The food is eloquent, melt in your mouth delicious. The drinks are top notch and the service in unparalleled. A huge thank you to our server Matthew for being a great waiter and guiding us through this amazing experience And thank you to the butchers chef. I definitely recommend you taking your significant other here for a delightful evening on the town ✔️ Cheers

name: Santravelz
snippet: Amazing Japanese wagyu and tasty roasted almond cake for dessert. Will try to visit again to do more dishes.

name: Ciro De Angelis
snippet: I was sitting at the bar and I ordered a seafood platter and a couple of cocktails. The bartender from Italy was very friendly and attentive. Great service and food!!

name: Timothy Rodrigues
snippet: Tried the tasting menu with wine pairings and it was absolutely worth every single cent I paid.

name: Kara Branton
snippet: Butcher Chef is unparalleled service and quality of food - an experience everyone should have at least once. One of my favourite spots!

name: Cathleen Scott
snippet: Beautiful dining experience. The food was prepared with great care and the staff were warm and professional.

name: Nathan K
snippet: Fantastic food and service. Great ambiance too. Best steak I’ve had in a while and the oysters were very fresh. Friendly, accommodating and warm while still being upscale. Portions are a good size and the food is tasty.

name: Rebecca Buchanan
snippet: Amazing appetizers, steaks, and great service. Highly recommend adding the bread service, was incredible.

name: Jacqueline Relke
snippet: I can not put into word how amazing my dining experience was at Butcher Chef. From the moment we walked in, the owner Michael and Sommelier Gordon took care of us like no other. The food, wine and staff are beyond exceptional. If you are looking to indulge and want to be treated like absolute royalty, you need to go

name: E ftied
snippet: Absolutely amazing service! Katya and Michael were so accommodating. Every attention to detail was made which made for a truly memorable experience. And of course the food was delicious. I will definitely be back

name: Jon Rohrich
snippet: Amazing restaurant. Fantastic space, remarkable service.... And the food... My God the food is incredible. Both the food and wine pairing were delectable. Go here, eat, drink. You won't regret it

name: Ron D
snippet: Ambiance was great, service was fine, but the quality of the food didn’t match the insane prices. If I’m paying $55 for 4 scallops and $25 for a cocktail, I want to be blown away. Instead, I walked away thinking “that wasn’t terrible.” I also mentioned to the hostess that I was pescatarian, and also repeated the restriction to the waiter, but wasn’t warned of seafood dishes that also contained meat.

name: Adrianna Fraser
snippet: Amazing. The bread was incredible and the steak, although I got the cheapest one($75) , was tender and perfect. Unlike any experience I’ve had before. I went with my boyfriend and he ordered a Japanese steak which was about $250 for the steak alone. He said his was amazing. We also had the carrots and asparagus and potatoes as sides. Would recommend getting just one side to share because they come in large portions on a separate plate. We went for our anniversary and would love to come back when we have the money lol

name: Kinga R-Z
snippet: This is one of the nicest places you can go to in Toronto; for a special time with a best friend, a colleague or a romantic night of magic memories. The staff go out of their way to make you feel welcome, special and they are on point. This is the real deal. Having dined in restaurants all over the world, including Dubai and Mexico City, NYC and London UK...I have the upmost confidence to encourage everyone to experience elegant dining at it's finest. Cuisine, Music, Decor, Atmosphere, Ambience...10/10.

name: MD
snippet: The service at this place was impeccable! From the moment you walk in, you’re greeted, they’ll take your coats for you, they explain all menu items. We were given an amuse-bouche, it was something we would have never ordered on our own - however it was so tasty & greatly appreciated! Daniel the host, and our server Robel were so nice and welcoming, we will definitely be back again!

name: Hiba A
snippet: Really disappointed with our dinning experience here. Expected much better for a restaurant of this caliber. The steaks were average. Once the food came out no server came to see if we needed anything or if the food was ok. We spoke to management about our experience and he did listen and compensated by offering us desserts on the house … however he did not ask if we had any dietary restrictions as some of the desserts had alcohol or gelatin which we do not eat. We basically had 4 desserts to compensate for the poor service and dinning experience half of which we weren’t able to eat. Would definitely not return or come back. Not worth the $300 bill.

name: gladys billups
snippet: Amazing foodie experience!!

name: Renato Sorbara
snippet: Another excellent dinner at Butcher Chef. We asked the wait staff to have the bartender surprise with some cocktails and what we got were 10/10 drinks. Amazing service, food and ambience. Highly recommended!

name: Tony
snippet: Food is excellent as always, although the jamon iberico from the charcuterie being no longer available is a bit of a bummer. There’s always a new drink to try every time, same goes for desserts, and a good number of entrees are also top notch. -2 because there was one employee? (dressed differently) who wasn’t our server came to our table after drinks and appetizer asking if we were ready for the bill. Ignoring the fact that our entrees were taking forever and have yet to come out, why is someone who isn’t even our server asking if we were ready to pay..? The same person held us back on our way out, informed us that there was a dress code and we should come dressed better next time. I hate to say it, you guys picked a location that’s literally the first floor of a residential building, 30 yards from a subway sandwiches and maybe 50 yards from the ramp homeless people live under. Plus if I’m spending half a grand on a meal, I’ll wear a t-shirt and joggers if I want to. I’ve also been here 4-5 times over the last year, I’ve worn literal basketball shorts in here before, never had an issue until premature bill guy. I’m here to eat good food with good company, not to uphold some image for you to the obnoxious table of eight 2’ behind me with laughs that can be heard over the sirens of a fire truck. While you’re giving me pointers on how to dress, you could also let some of your other guests know that they’re not here to record the laugh tracks for a sitcom

name: Nicole Godin
snippet: Highly recommended! I visited The Butcher Chef with my boyfriend on a night out for his birthday and we were both thoroughly impressed. One of the best steakhouses in the city and some of the best service and food you'll experience. All the dishes we tried were beyond our expectations. The morel mushroom salad and the tuna & A5 tartare are a definite must have. The restaurant was beautifully decorated and provided an intimate and whimsical ambiance. The service from the moment we walked in to the time we left was consistently welcoming and professional. We will definitely be visiting again sometime soon.

name: Matthew McGarr
snippet: The Butcher Chef was phenomenal. The wild shrimp ceviche was refreshing and a perfect start to the meal. I tried the PEI Tenderloin and it was cooked to perfection, very flavourful. The portion sizes were also good - a big highlight in my opinion. For dessert, the espresso martini is a must try. Service is top class, and the decor’s beautiful. Would recommend to anyone!

name: Ioanna B
snippet: Ordered their Thanksgiving meal (turkey/beef Wellington) and was so impressed. It was enough food for two separate dinners so we did just that and everyone was amazed. I was also really impressed with the staff, the hostess met me at the parking lot to show me where to go and the chef actually carried the meals to my car. We will happily become regulars here!

name: Natasha Sansone
snippet: Thank you to the Butcher Chef for a fabulous experience! It was an absolute treat to be able to get back out for an evening of fine dining and whining. The staff was attentive and friendly, we received a coursed tasting menu which was both delicious and original, the presentation was elegant. The new patio has an intimate and stylish feel, definitely the new gem of downtown Toronto! Will be back soon. X

name: David Shafrir
snippet: Best steak house in Toronto hands down. Top notch service with a personal touch makes dinner at Butcher Chef an incredible experience every time. The patio is well protected and proper so even during the pandemic, dining is a great overall experience.

name: Nina Vaia
snippet: Food was amazing, you pay for what you get. Steak was cooked perfectly but was pretty oversalted, very tender and juicy but also very very rich. Staff was lovely, place was very clean right down to the bathrooms.

name: Jessica Linton
snippet: To say that the Butcher Chef paid fine attention to detail when creating their dining experience is an understatement. From the decor, to the service, to the food itself, nothing was left to be desired. As someone who used to work in the restaurant industry, I was blown away by the product knowledge and overall etiquette of the serving staff. The Shrimp Ceviche is a must as well as the Espresso Martini, which the owner, Michael Dabic, has told me he has been perfecting for years. It was an exemplary finish to the meal. I highly recommend for a celebration or just a casual night out on the town.

name: Marnee Bruno
snippet: What an absolutely gorgeous meal! We had the tasting menu and it was truly a culinary feast. Such a range of deliciousness with each dish bringing us further down the road of delight. From the most delicate fish, to perfectly braised duck, rabbit, raviolini al tartuffo and o my gosh the waigu beef was quite possibly the best I’ve ever tasted. We started with a beautiful violet cocktail and finished this treat with the affogato - chef Derrick outdid himself.

name: S M
snippet: Definitely one of a kind for this city! Feels like you're in an intimate VIP restaurant in NYC. The level of service & respect take VIP to the next level. Chef is by far one of the best in this city, amongst others.... needless to say the quality of food, taste & presentation, is to die for! The atmosphere, decor & attention to detail is breathtaking. This place is beyond Michelin Star quality! Definitely a must see on the restaurant foodie checklist!

name: BERNARD WOLF
snippet: Amazing food and impeccable service in an elegant contemporary setting at this relatively new restaurant emphasizing steak, but with a much wider menu. We shared a magnificent Argentinian dry aged ribeye steak cooked medium rare to perfection. The accompanying oyster mushrooms and heirloom salad were outstanding. Although expensive, it is worth the money. My only criticism is there could be better signage identifying the restaurant so that it is easier to find.

name: Frank Battiston
snippet: Amazing food. Exceptional service. Beautiful interior. A group of us did the tasting menu with wine pairings and it was perfect. Every dish was both original and delicious, with exquisite attention paid to all culinary details. Best New Restaurant in Toronto? Easily. Best Restaurant in Toronto? Possibly. Highly recommended.

name: Mira Linton
snippet: Outstanding! Dined with my family a few nights ago, wonderful meal and experience. Service was excellent, beautiful patio and interior. Wild shrimp ceviche appetizer is a must try. Looking forward to returning!

name: JP Chavez
snippet: 24oz PEI Prime Ribeye was cooked to perfection aka medium rare. Lol. The potatoes and leeks was deliciously creamy. Also had some cheese and chive macarons and a beef tartare with seaweed that were quite different. But it did strike the pallet in a good way. They went with a vinaigrette based Caesar salad and was genius. Creme Brule was a little over cooked, wasn't as creamy as it should of been but the taste was still excellent. Nothing but good news and good food here. Obviously, its the sister restaurant of Michael's on Simcoe.

name: Sherry Hamilton
snippet: Excellent customer service! Whenever I needed something they were there for me. Thank you guys

name: Danny H
snippet: I had dinner last week with a friend and it was outstanding. The attention to detail is remarkable, Chef Derek has outdone himself. We tasted most items on the menu and each one was delicious and prepared perfectly. I can’t stop talking about this place! My new favourite dining room in TORONTO. It’s nice to have an option so close to Scotia arena pre-game / post-game dinner. 2 min walk to the arena. Amazing food and drinks. These guys put together a perfect new restaurant.

name: Joe J
snippet: Boutique style restaurant with excellent food & service. Nice restaurant for a special occasion or meeting.

name: Jasmine Car
snippet: We pre ordered over the phone, and came in to pick up our order, although they do deliver. We wanted to take a quick peak of the restaurant inside as it is fairly new. This restaurant has such a lovely ambiance, and we can't wait to dine in! Our order was customized, and they took care of every little detail. We had several different kind of steaks (family of 6) cooked to our perfect temperature preference. The seasoning was impeccably on point. We had several different sides, all of which were absolutely incredible. There's nothing worse than being in the mood for steak and not being happy with your order (Sadly I've experienced this many times at other restaurants). This place did not dissappoint & is a must try for any steak lover. We are looking forward to sampling more....the bbq box on the menu sounds perfect for our patio staycation this weekend!

name: Peter Dabic

name: James Nulis
snippet: Last Saturday, my wife and I went to The Butcher Chef for the first time. We've dined at Michael's On Simcoe numerous times and have always had an amazing experience so we were anticipating another wonderful evening. The Butcher Chef, did not disappoint. It's a intimate yet approachable setting with luxury finishes throughout; no detail was overlooked. The menu is concise and well thought with a comprehensive wine list with options for everyone. We were offered the bread coarse by the knowledgeable and friendly staff; it's an absolute must have! It's brioche loaf, the manager or wait staff will elegantly pour melted gruyere cheese on the top and finish it with a zest of cured meat. It's to die for. Enjoy. For our appetizers, we had the Heirloom Salad and Tuna & A5 Wagyu Tartare; both dishes we're prepared nicely and we're delicious. Would definitely recommend the Tartare. For our entrees, we split the San-Luis Argentina 14oz Ribeye. The waiter was very helpful throughout the evening, helping us navigate the menu and choices. When it came to Steaks, he was extremely valuable. He knew his cuts and regions well to help ensure we made the best decision for our palates. Sides, Shishito Peppers with Spiced Goat Cheese & Pastrami Smoked Carrots. We typically don't go for Carrots at restaurants but they were worth the "gamble". Very good and would recommend you try them. Desert, we had Salted Caramel Creme Brulee which was delicious. I would highly recommend The Butcher Chef for any occasion; it's a place to celebrate a special occasion or to catch up with friends / family.

name: Tom ROkicki

Given that this establishment is in the middle of downtown with no shortage of culinary competition, I had a great experience here. The décor is top notch and gives and the food is at the same level. It was close proximity to Scotiabank Center so I see it giving Harbor 60 a run for its money.
